New World Wealth has recently published a ranking of the top golf estates in South Africa. The report is based on a number of visits by the New World Wealth team to top estates across the country. According to SA real estate advisor Basil Weinrich – who helped compile the ratings – residential estate living is on the rise, especially among the more affluent. He estimates that over 40% of South African HNWIs live or have homes on residential estates. The ratings were based on the following criteria: Communal gardens and parks;
Design and space;
Maintenance;
Location, views and scenery;
Security features;
Activities and facilities available on the estate;
Condition of course;
Memorability of course;
Clubhouse, change rooms and halfway house facilities;
